<paragraph blockId="5.[264,707,1710,1736]" box="[264,707,1710,1736]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<heading bold="true" box="[264,707,1710,1736]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,707,1710,1736]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Monterosato, 1884" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1884" box="[351,707,1710,1736]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Pagodula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,467,1710,1736]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Pagodula</emphasis>
Monterosato, 
<number box="[648,707,1710,1736]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="1884.0">1884</number>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1321,1785,1891]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
The 
<typeStatus box="[318,368,1785,1811]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[505,619,1785,1810]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Pagodula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[505,619,1785,1810]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Pagodula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was wrongly cited by Radwin &amp; D’ Attilio (
<number box="[1158,1222,1785,1811]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="1975.0">1975</number>
: 
<number box="[1235,1280,1785,1811]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="285.0">285</number>
) as being 
<taxonomicName authority="Cristofori &amp; Jan, 1832" authorityName="Cristofori &amp; Jan" authorityYear="1832" box="[342,838,1825,1851]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vaginatus">
<emphasis box="[342,544,1825,1850]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Murex vaginatus</emphasis>
Cristofori &amp; Jan, 
<number box="[779,838,1825,1851]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="1832.0">1832</number>
</taxonomicName>
by original designation, and later, that citation was wrongly considered a subsequent designation by 
<bibRefCitation author="Houart" box="[987,1216,1865,1891]" pageId="5" pageNumber="67" refString="Houart, R. (2001) Ingensia gen. nov. and eleven new species of Muricidae (Gastropoda) from New Caledonia, Vanuatu, and Wallis and Futuna Islands. Tropical Deep-Sea Benthos, vol. 22. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 185, 243 - 269." type="book chapter" year="2001">
Houart (
<number box="[1084,1148,1865,1891]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="2001.0">2001</number>
: 
<number box="[1159,1207,1865,1891]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" value="130.0">130</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1325,284,710]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
Monterosato’ s extension of 
<taxonomicName box="[653,849,284,309]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis box="[653,849,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Murex carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included both the Pleistocene fossil for which the names 
<taxonomicName authority="Bivona, 1832" authorityName="Bivona" authorityYear="1832" box="[477,846,324,350]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis box="[477,674,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Murex carinatus</emphasis>
Bivona, 
<number box="[787,846,324,350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1832.0">1832</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cristofori &amp; Jan, 1832" authorityName="Cristofori &amp; Jan" authorityYear="1832" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vaginatus">
<emphasis box="[908,1108,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Murex vaginatus</emphasis>
Cristofori &amp; Jan, 
<number box="[264,323,364,390]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1832.0">1832</number>
</taxonomicName>
[which he cited in synonymy] are available, and the Recent form described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Kiener, 1840" authorityName="Kiener" authorityYear="1840" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="echinatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Fusus echinatus</emphasis>
Kiener, 
<number box="[483,542,404,430]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1840.0">1840</number>
</taxonomicName>
[which he also cited in synonymy]. The Pleistocene and Recent forms have since been found to represent different species, differing in particular by their protoconchs (
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet" box="[423,705,484,510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1985) Revision of the Northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Neogastropoda excluding Turridae. Bollettino Malacologico, suppl. 1, 123 - 296." type="journal article" year="1985">
Bouchet &amp; Warén 
<number box="[644,705,484,510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="La" box="[717,893,484,510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refString="La Perna, R. (1996) Phyletic and ecological implications between Pagodula vaginata (De Cristofori &amp; Jan, 1832) and Pagodula echinata (Kiener, 1840) (Gastropoda, Muricidae). Bollettino della Societa Paleontologica Italiana, 35, 81 - 92." type="journal article" year="1996">
La Perna 
<number box="[830,893,484,510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This is a case of misidentified 
<typeStatus box="[1274,1325,484,510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">type</typeStatus>
species covered by Art. 
<number box="[551,602,524,550]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="70.3">70.3</number>
of the Code. To lift the ambiguity in the identity of the 
<typeStatus box="[1272,1323,524,550]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[391,505,564,589]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Pagodula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[391,505,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Pagodula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and because it better serves the purpose of taxonomical research to have the Recent form as 
<typeStatus box="[568,618,604,630]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">type</typeStatus>
species, we here select under Art. 
<number box="[1045,1096,604,630]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="70.3">70.3</number>
as 
<typeStatus box="[1141,1191,604,630]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Monterosato, 1884" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1884" box="[264,607,644,670]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Pagodula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,378,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Pagodula</emphasis>
Monterosato, 
<number box="[548,607,644,670]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1884.0">1884</number>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Kiener, 1840" authorityName="Kiener" authorityYear="1840" box="[613,964,644,670]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="echinatus">
<emphasis box="[613,802,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Fusus echinatus</emphasis>
Kiener, 
<number box="[903,964,644,670]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1840.0">1840</number>
</taxonomicName>
, misidentified by Monterosato as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bivona, 1832" authorityName="Bivona" authorityYear="1832" box="[296,658,684,710]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis box="[296,489,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Murex carinatus</emphasis>
Bivona, 
<number box="[596,658,684,710]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" value="1832.0">1832</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
